---
description: After code changes, commit, push, and deploy to Vercel; document DB migrations when schema changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git — always push changes

When a task **changes, adds, or deletes** files in this project (including edits made by the AI in Cursor), **always finish with commit + push** — not only when the user asks:

1. From the project root (`zing`): `git status`
2. If there are changes: `git add` the relevant paths (or `git add -A` when appropriate)
3. `git commit -m "Short imperative description of what changed"`
4. `git push origin main`

**Do not** leave committed work unpushed unless the user explicitly asks to wait or skip push. **Do not** stop after commit without attempting push.

If push fails (auth, network), give the user the **exact commands** to run in Terminal.

If there is **nothing to commit**, say so briefly — no empty commit.

# Vercel — always deploy production (direct)

**Telnyx** = telephony (numbers, voice). **Vercel** = where the Next.js app is hosted (e.g. getzingapp.com). Pushing code live for users means deploying on **Vercel**, not “pushing to Telnyx.”

After a successful **commit** in the same task (when there was something to ship), **also** deploy production from the project root:

5. `npm run deploy:vercel`  
   (uses the linked project in `.vercel/` — production build + alias)

Run this even when `git push` failed, so production still updates. If deploy fails (not logged in, network), give the **exact command** and error so the user can run `npx vercel login` locally if needed. Allow enough time for the remote build (often 1–3 minutes).

If there was **no commit** in the task, skip deploy unless the user asked to deploy only.

# Database (Neon) — update when needed

- **Agents cannot connect to Neon** from this environment. Never claim the production DB was migrated unless the user ran SQL in Neon.
- If you **add or change** `scripts/*.sql` or change what `lib/db.ts` expects (new table/column), **update `scripts/MIGRATE-ALL.md`** (and **`PRODUCTION.md`** if the setup story changes), then tell the user to open **Neon → SQL Editor** and run the new script(s).
- If the user hits save/routing errors about missing tables or columns, point them to **`scripts/MIGRATE-ALL.md`** and the numbered scripts listed there.
